Sitting at the beach today and this is what i came up with! The moons reflection shining upon the water that is slowly moving towards the shore. Glistening, glowing, so peaceful, so at ease. Nature at its best. The waves quietly connecting with the shore, gently pulling back the rocks that were once there. The smashing crackle, with the wind caressing the ripples on the surface. Moving as one, but together at the same time. The wind is growing stronger, starting to forcefully move the water. The wind is not visible like the moons reflection, or the stars that are guiding our way, but it is strong. AS strong as the emotions that breeze through me as my eyes meet yours. Your reflection is beautiful, you are as strong as the wind, but as calm as the current, and YOUR star is guiding my way. ......what do you think...? hmm not sure, sooooo went to a stupid don west meeting, was pointless i could get taht paper anytime...but its fine always nice to see everyone, ummmmmmm i saw leals underwear that was a highlight of my night, i changed my voicemail, and since 6:00 this is what i ate...Big Mac, fish sandwich, hot dog, chicken quesadilla hot pocket, and a chicked caeser salad wrap...OMG i am a fat kid yikes, good thing we are going to be on a hard core work out schedule, and some yoga on the side(IT"S SO GOOD!!!) zompetti kills me! im out of here youngins p.s. i love amy sacky p.p.s i love softball p.p.p.s i love ?

somewhere i have never travelled

somewhere i have never travelled, gladly beyond 
any experience, your eyes have their silence: 
in your most frail gesture are things which enclose me, 
or which i cannot touch because they are too near 

your slightest look easily will unclose me 
though i have closed myself as fingers, 
you open always petal by petal myself as Spring opens 
(touching skillfully, mysteriously) her first rose 

or if your wish be to close me, i and 
my life will shut very beautifully, suddenly, 
as when the heart of this flower imagines 
the snow carefully everywhere descending; 

nothing which we are to perceive in this world equals 
the power of your intense fragility whose texture 
compels me with the colour of its countries, 
rendering death and forever with each breathing 

(i do not know what it is about you that closes 
and opens; only something in me understands 
the voice of your eyes is deeper than all roses) 
nobody, not even the rain, has such small hands 

e. e. cummings, 1894-1962
